volume.name: Walt Disney's Comics- Wheaties Set C
Walt Disney's Donald Duck in The Case of the Missing Mummy

description: The 1999 NATO bombing of Serbia. A grenade shell from a Sarajevo souvenir shop. A refrigerator with the frozen mummy of Tito... These serve as the starting point for a journey further and further down the collective unconscious of the Balkans, where the borders between dream and reality are erased and redrawn until they form a tale as exciting as it is fantastic, a tale which could be about our times and a war-torn Europe but just as well might be a deep dive into the psyches of its authors or a discussion about the essence of drawing. Bosnian Flat Dog is the result of a unique collaboration between two of Sweden's most internationally renowned cartoonists, Death and Candy and Pixy creator Max Andersson and Lars Sjunnesson. Each of them contributed to every single drawing to the extent that they no longer can tell themselves exactly who did what. This has lead to the emergence of an independent artistic entity which is neither of the two, but something else, at once familiar and unknown and perhaps a little bit scary.
The story you've been waiting for! "Blow-Back" tells the story of how Captain Thunder was framed for a crime he didn't commit.
name: Blow-back

description: The penultimate chapter of the "Merchants of Menace" saga. Captain Thunder and Blue Bolt come face-to-face with a man who was supposed to be dead.
name: Hard Targets

description: A comic to benefit the Hero Initiative, featuring all-new stories by some of the best creators in comics! Fantastic features include: An original Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles short story, a Zombies vs. Robots extravaganza, a new Rex Mantooth Kung-Fu Gorilla story, plus more! And this book will also present single page stories by comics creators who have personally benefitted from the Hero Initiative!

The post-apocalyptic Dungeons & Dragons setting's first-ever comic! Beneath a crimson sun lie wastelands of majestic desolation and cities of cruel splendor, where life hangs by a thread. Welcome to Athas! When an imprisoned gladiator named Grudvik escapes the city of Tyr, a part-time slave hunter and full-time dune trader is hired to bring back the fugitive. But after crossing swords, the pair must join forces to survive the harsh desert.
name: TPB

description: My name's Akemi, number 29 to my keepers at the Citadel. The Citadel may be everybody's dream, but it is my nightmare. That is until he showed up. Who he is I don't know, but maybe he can do what nobody's ever done before - escape the Citadel and give me the chance for freedom. First though on his agenda, find somebody named Loki, and second, try and figure out why he didn't die in something called Ragnarok?

description: Tarzan finds himself the prey in a jungle hunt led by a blowhard Yankee mogul named Sykes. Several bodies and a series of mind games later, Sykes' plan unfolds: bring the captive ape-man to New York City for the Match of the Century against undefeated master of the fighting arts, Starker the Suplative!

description:
Jughead gets cursed with Jinx Malloy’s bad luck hex in this zany adventure that will have you in stitches! Will Jughead manage to rid himself of this unlucky spell before it becomes permanent or will he be destined to dish out poor fortune wherever he goes?

Jughead's baby sister feels that Jughead is ashamed of her but later on, Jughead finds out the advantages of having a baby sister.

Whenever the prizes are burgers, Jughead wins!
name: Luck, Flee A Lady/Babe Magnet/The Expert

description: Crime is at an all-time high. Wars, disease, and drugs run rampant. At the center of this corruption is Korath, an immortal being with an unquenchable thirst for dominance. I am the one that prevents his victory, I am the Acolyte. On the streets of Argent, the battle will escalate.
